			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Adding Uncertainty and Units to Quantity Types in Software Models</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/TanjaMayerhofer.html">Tanja Mayerhofer</a>, <a href="../profile/ManuelWimmer.html">Manuel Wimmer</a>, <a href="../profile/AntonioVallecillo.html">Antonio Vallecillo</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997376">10.1145/2997364.2997376</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagM">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It extends type systems with units and uncertainty to improve static semantics of quantity types.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1a.html"><span class="tagL">T1A: Design</span></a><ul><li> The paper proposes language/type design extensions to modeling languages for physical quantities.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6f.html"><span class="tagL">T6F: CPS/IoT/DT</span></a><ul><li> Units and measurement uncertainty are central in CPS/engineering domains where physical quantities matter.
</li></ul></li></ul>
